<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="187" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d187">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Butler</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico
                                        City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-17"><hi rend="italic">July 17,
                                1895</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to Department’s 45, of 8th instant. Forsee here and located
                            Chester Rowe. Latter assumed Mexican nationality by purchase real
                            estate, thus protected from extradition. See article 6 extradition
                            treaty, article 30 Mexican federal constitution, and article 1, section
                            10, law on foreigners, reported by legation’s 241, June 10, 1886. Please
                            instruct me.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Butler.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>